extends ../layout

block content

  .step#title
    h1 How to tell stories with data
    h3.bottom0 Digital Journalism Bootcamp
    p Tunis 2012 - Pierre Romera - <a href="http://twitter.com/pirhoo">@pirhoo</a>


  .step(data-x=990)
    h2 Get started with a definition*
    blockquote All activities related to the preparation of a newspaper or any other newspaper or magazine or audiovisual (<big><strong>collecting</strong></big>, <big><strong>selecting</strong></big>, <big><strong>formatting information</strong></big>) [...]
    ol.footnotes
      li Larousse dictionary <a href="http://www.larousse.fr/dictionnaires/francais/journalisme">http://www.larousse.fr/dictionnaires/francais/journalisme</a> [FR]

  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  //- COLLECTING
  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  .step(data-x=990*2)
    h2 Collect
    p 
      | It's one of my favorite point, as a developer.<br />
      strong For a long time, journalists have to gather information.
    h3 But why is it so suitable?

  .step(data-x=990*2, data-y=400*1, data-rotate-x=-10)
    h3.bottom10 Take a look to the last decade
    p.bottom10 Never before the information's sources have been so many.
    p.bottom10 Never before the information have circulated so easily.
    p Vox pops have become tweets. Messages circulate at 5 Mbps.
    h3.bottom10 Coming after the digital natives,<br />we are now in a world of data natives.
    p Swiming at any time in a global data ocean.
  
  .step(data-x=990*2, data-y=400*2, data-rotate-x=-10*2)
    h3.bottom0 We produce a lot of passive data
    p Credit cards, mobile phone, video games, fidelity cards, ...
    h3 Since a few year, <big>citizens</big> are begining to be active producers of data.

  .step(data-x=990*2, data-y=400*3, data-rotate-x=-10*3)
    h2.bottom10 <small>Everyday,</small> Facebook's users<small><br />produce the equivalent of <br /></small>120,000 DVD discs <small>of data</small>*
    p Just 2 days to cover a soccer field.
    ol.footnotes
      li Le Monde Informatique, August 2012 <a href="http://www.lemondeinformatique.fr/actualites/lire-facebook-supporte-500-to-de-nouvelles-donnees-par-jour-50140.html">http://bit.ly/P3mQns</a> [FR]

  .step(data-x=990*2, data-y=400*4, data-rotate-x=-10*4)
    h3 That's what we call<br /><big>User Generated Contents<big>.
    p 
      | Videos on YouTube, Tweets, Likes, Twitpics, <br />
      | are a <big>new material</big> for Journalists.

  .step(data-x=990*2, data-y=400*5, data-rotate-x=-10*5)
    h3.tc The <big>nature</big> of the information<br />had changed.      

  .step(data-x=990*2, data-y=400*5, data-rotate-x=-10*5, data-rotate-y=180)
    h3.tc The <big>ways</big> to collect&nbsp;information had changed too.

  .step(data-x=990*2, data-y=400*6, data-rotate-x=-10*6)
    h3 Collective inteligence       
    p.bottom15.left20 Every single person has limited knowledges of its environement.
    p.bottom15.left60 Collective inteligence tries to <strong>gather these pieces of individuality</strong> arround a common issue.
    p.bottom15.left100 It defines the rules, the target, and the shape of every contributions.
   

  .step(data-x=990*2, data-y=400*6+1500, data-rotate-x=-10*6, data-z=1000)
    a(href="http://feowl.com") 
      img.thumbnail(src="/images/feowl.png", alt="")



  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  //- SELECTING
  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  .step(data-x=990*3)
    h2 Select
    p Once journalists are aware to that world of data,<br />they have to consider it like any other information.
    h3 Manage with data it's like dealing with any source.

  .step(data-x=990*3, data-y=400*1, data-rotate-x=-10)
    h3.bottom0 <big>WikiLeaks</big><br />is an interesting subject
    p This organization aims to expose the truth about the governments. <strong>Know the intentions of a source is a central point</strong>.

  .step(data-x=990*3, data-y=400*2, data-rotate-x=-10*2)
    .row-fluid
      .span4
        img(src="/images/ja-london.JPG", alt="Reuter").thumbnail
      .span8
        p.left20
          | To work, WikiLeaks needs to ensure the anonymity of its <em>Wistle Blowers</em>. <strong>It's both an opportunity and a problematic point for the journalists.</strong>

  .step(data-x=990*3, data-y=400*3, data-rotate-x=-10*3)
    h3.bottom0 An opportunity
    p because the organization has the perfect tool to reach the deepest secrets.
    p With WikiLeaks we can touch a <strong>proximity matter</strong> increasingly difficult to reach.


  .step(data-x=990*3, data-y=400*3, data-rotate-x=-10*3, data-rotate-y=180)
    h3.bottom0 A problematic point
    p because to juge properly a material, we need to completely evaluate its source.
    p How else distinguish these documents from hallway noises or conspiracy?

  .step(data-x=990*3, data-y=400*4, data-rotate-x=-10*4)
    h3 OF COURSE A NEWSROOM CAN'T CHECK EVERY LINE OF EVERY DATASET

  .step(data-x=990*3, data-y=400*5, data-rotate-x=-10*5)
    h3.bottom0 The paradox is still complexe
    h4 We have to apply the same vigilance with the Open Government policies. 

 



  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  //- FORMATING
  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  .step(data-x=990*4)
    h2 Format  
    p Now, you have data.